  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F.",
    "Mix flour, baking powder, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Add olive oil and mix until smooth.",
    "Dip snapper fillets into the flour mixture, ensuring they're well coated.",
    "Place coated fillets onto an earthenware bowl lined with parchment paper.",
    "Sprinkle sesame seeds over fish.",
    "If desired, sprinkle chili flakes on top for added kick.",
    "Broil in preheated oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown and crispy.",
    "Serve hot as a midnight craving dish."
